A powerful cyclone hit Bangladesh and India, prompting mass evacuations.
Officials fear severe damage to property and infrastructure.
The storm, reminiscent of past deadly cyclones, poses a significant threat.
The United States and Germany have offered emergency relief aid.
The cyclone has already claimed many lives and left thousands homeless.
Efforts are underway to provide shelter, clean water, and medical assistance to the affected.
The international community is rallying to support relief efforts.
The focus is on providing food and aid to those in need amidst the devastation caused by Cyclone Sidr.
